cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically on enhancing the performance of 1-bit DCNNs. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new balanced Genetic Algorithm (BGA) to optimize the 1-bit DCNNs, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses object recognition tasks, which can be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia).
